mplify select_idle_sibling(), which is clearly way too random.<br /><br />That is, if we could make it automatic, some way. Not the "let the<br />user tune it" - that's just fundamentally broken.<br /><br />What is the common pattern for the wakeups for psql?<br /><br />Can we detect this somehow? Are they sync? It looks wrong to preempt<br />for sync wakeups, for example, but we seem to do that.<br /><br />Or could we just improve the heuristics. What happens if the<br />scheduling granularity is increased, for example? It's set to 1ms<br />right now, with a logarithmic scaling by number of cpus.<br /><br />        Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
